==English==
=== Etymology ===
from Middle English, from Old French [[archier]], from Late Latin [[arcarius]], ''alteration of'' [[arcuarius]], from Latin [[arcus]], ''bow''.
=== Noun ===
'''archer''' ([[archers]])

# one who shoots an arrow from a bow or a bolt from a crossbow.

